**GDPR Compliance Script Development**

**Introduction**

This script is designed to create a form that accepts and saves user-inputted text for GDPR compliance purposes. The form will collect information on data protection, data transfer, and data subject rights.

**Form Development**

```javascript
// Import necessary libraries
const express = require('express');
const bodyParser = require('body-parser');

// Create an Express app
const app = express();

// Use body-parser middleware to parse JSON bodies
app.use(bodyParser.json());

// Define the form structure
const formStructure = {
  "dataProtection": {
    "type": "text",
    "label": "Data Protection Policy"
  },
  "dataTransfer": {
    "type": "text",
    "label": "Data Transfer Policy"
  },
  "dataSubjectRights": {
    "type": "text",
    "label": "Data Subject Rights Policy"
  }
};

// Create a form object to store user input
const form = {};

// Function to handle form submission
function handleSubmit(req, res) {
  // Get user input from the request body
  const userInput = req.body;

  // Validate user input
  if (Object.keys(userInput).length === 0) {
    res.status(400).send("Please fill out the form");
  } else {
    // Save user input to the form object
    form.dataProtection = userInput.dataProtection;
    form.dataTransfer = userInput.dataTransfer;
    form.dataSubjectRights = userInput.dataSubjectRights;

    // Save the form object to a database or file
    // For demonstration purposes, we'll just log the form object to the console
    console.log(form);

    // Send a success response to the user
    res.status(200).send("Form submitted successfully");
  }
}

// Create a route for the form submission
app.post('/submit', handleSubmit);

// Create a route for the form
app.get('/form', (req, res) => {
  // Render the form template with the form structure
  res.render('form', { formStructure });
});

// Start the server
const port = 3000;
app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Server started on port ${port}`);
});
```

